        <html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi (a | s)]]></fr:tex> is trained via <fr:link href="/OGCSB/" title="Empirical risk minimization" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/OGCSB/" display-uri="OGCSB" type="local">ERM</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s \sim  d^{\pi _{\beta }}(s)]]></fr:tex> and optimal labels <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a^*]]></fr:tex>, and attains generalizationerror <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s \sim  d^{\pi _{\beta }}(s)]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ell (\pi ) \leq  C + H^2 \epsilon ]]></fr:tex> is the best possible bound.</html:p>
